{'book': {'publisher': 'Pearson College Div', 'synopsis': 'This book explores the standard problem-solving techniques of multivariable mathematics ? integrating vector algebra ideas with multivariable calculus and differential equations. Provides many routine, computational exercises illuminating both theory and practice. Offers flexibility in coverage ? topics can be covered in a variety of orders, and subsections (which are presented in order of decreasing importance) can be omitted if desired. Provides proofs and includes the definitions and statements of theorems to show how the subject matter can be organized around a few central ideas. Includes new sections on: flow lines and flows; centroids and moments; arc-length and curvature; improper integrals; quadratic surfaces; infinite series?with application to differential equations; and numerical methods. Presents refined method for solving linear systems using exponential matrices.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/64/59/9780131816459.jpg', 'title_long': 'Multivariable Mathematics (3rd Edition)', 'edition': 'Subsequent', 'dimensions': 'Height: 9.75 Inches, Length: 8.5 Inches, Weight: 3.17906581804 Pounds, Width: 1.25 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.5}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 1.25}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 3.17906581804}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 9.75}}, 'pages': 680, 'date_published': '1995-11-28', 'subjects': ['Science & Math', 'Mathematics', 'Applied', 'Pure Mathematics', 'Specialty Boutique', 'New, Used & Rental Textbooks'], 'authors': ['Richard E. Williamson', 'Hale F. Trotter'], 'title': 'Multivariable Mathematics (3rd Edition)', 'isbn13': '9780131816459', 'msrp': 1.99, 'binding': 'Hardcover', 'isbn': '0131816454', 'isbn10': '0131816454'}}